line_1: Then parting, at my feet they bend, and clasp
line_2: These aged knees — my soul yet feels their grasp!

line_1: To all in life its love would clasp
I live within my arms to clasp,
This hand no longer thine shall clasp;
line_2: To-morrow, chill'd by death's cold grasp,

line_1: His little arms his mother clasp.
line_2: He struggles from the stranger's grasp:
